; 6:20). </div><div class="t m452 x45 h1a y862 ff1 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">IV. </div><div class="t m7ea x56 h1a ya82 ff1 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Paul&apos;s Greeting and Farewell (Eph. 1:2; 6:23, 24). </div><div class="t m4d9 xa6 h56 ya83 ff3 fs1c fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Second Lesson: </div><div class="t m5ac xa6 h1b y617 ff4 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">THE BLESSINGS OF THE BELIEVER </div><div class="t m58a x12 h1b ya86 ff4 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">MEMORY </div><div class="t m2ac x14 h1a y9de ff1 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">TEXT: Eph. 1:10. </div><div class="t m144 x12 h1a ycd4 ff1 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">THIS WEEK&apos;S STUDY: Eph. 1:3-14. </div><div class="t m32b x12 h1a y9e1 ff1 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">CENTRAL THOUGHT: God has a plan that is all-inclusive. He longs </div><div class="t m289 xa6 h1a y9e2 ff1 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">to unite every created being into one body. We can be thankful that His </div><div class="t m2c4 xa6 h1a ycd5 ff1 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">plan is so comprehensive that it includes each one of us individually. </div><div class="t m2c xa6 h1a y12 ff1 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">OUTLINE: </div><div class="t m7e9 x3b h1a ya88 ff1 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">I. </div><div class="t m248 x56 h1a yc07 ff1 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Prelude of Praise (Eph. 1:3). </div><div class="t m51c x4f h1a y9a2 ff1 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">II. </div><div class="t m4a5 x56 h1a y9a3 ff1 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Thankful for Being Chosen—Election (Eph. 1:4-6). </div><div class="t md0 x22 h1a ycd6 ff1 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">III. </div><div class="t m118 x56 h1a y7bf ff1 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Thankful for Being Rescued—Redemption (Eph. 1:7). </div><div class="t m452 x45 h1a y9a4 ff1 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">IV. </div><div class="t m48c x56 h1a y9e6 ff1 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Thankful to God for His Inheritance—Restoration (Eph. 1:8-14). </div><div class="t m228 xa6 h56 y18 ff3 fs1c fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Lessons in Braille: </div><div class="t m6b3 x3c h1a y66c ff1 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The regular Adult Sabbath School Lessons are available free 